\f0\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Ps::0>
\f1\fs32 Most generators are <term>self-excited</term>, meaning that the excitation current is derived from the power produced by the generator. Starting of a self-excited generator makes use of the residual permanent magnetism of the field core. Once the generator starts rotating, the residual permanent magnetism induces current to begin to excite the field coils, and the resulting magnetic flux builds up to the desired level.\

